00:33:51,120 --> 00:33:53,140
because I wish to bear
responsibilities for it myself.

563
00:34:07,730 --> 00:34:09,020
I heard

564
00:34:09,160 --> 00:34:11,500
that you formed a team behind my back.

565
00:34:12,080 --> 00:34:13,460
What's with that?

566
00:34:13,760 --> 00:34:15,540
You don't want to take me with you now?

567
00:34:16,760 --> 00:34:18,420
You're all independent now, huh?

568
00:34:19,530 --> 00:34:21,980
My legs will recover soon.

569
00:34:22,560 --> 00:34:25,310
Now that she's leaving,
you should reserve a slot for me.

570
00:34:26,490 --> 00:34:28,150
I already reserved the last slot

571
00:34:29,490 --> 00:34:31,020
for you.

572
00:34:33,370 --> 00:34:35,310
That's more like it.

573
00:34:35,490 --> 00:34:36,710
You're my buddy indeed.

574
00:34:37,490 --> 00:34:38,860
But listen,

575
00:34:39,050 --> 00:34:41,350
the Yinshaluo Tribe is truly impressive.

576
00:34:41,810 --> 00:34:43,380
They're not afraid of death at all.

577
00:34:43,760 --> 00:34:45,049
All of them came to me

578
00:34:45,050 --> 00:34:47,190
saying that they wanted
to join the team.

579
00:34:47,680 --> 00:34:49,230
I said no way.

580
00:34:49,760 --> 00:34:50,759
I asked them

581
00:34:50,760 --> 00:34:52,830
if they had no family members
or relatives here.

582
00:34:53,850 --> 00:34:55,409
One of them

583
00:34:55,410 --> 00:34:57,710
had a beautiful wife too.

584
00:34:58,410 --> 00:35:00,310
Look at the situation we're in.

585
00:35:00,530 --> 00:35:02,460
You're still determined
despite your injuries, huh?

586
00:35:04,560 --> 00:35:07,350
Do I look like that kind
of person to you?

587
00:35:07,560 --> 00:35:09,060
You didn't see it for yourself.

588
00:35:09,240 --> 00:35:11,239
They haven't weaned their child yet.

589
00:35:11,240 --> 00:35:13,049
We can't just let
the child be fatherless

590
00:35:13,050 --> 00:35:14,160
after his birth, right?

591
00:35:14,160 --> 00:35:15,840
I told him that
he wasn't allowed to join us.

592
00:35:16,080 --> 00:35:19,020
If you join us, your family
will be in terrible shape.

593
00:35:19,050 --> 00:35:21,559
He was a burly man,
yet he cried on the spot.

594
00:35:21,560 --> 00:35:23,049
Unlike the Zhang Family.

595
00:35:23,050 --> 00:35:24,540
They're heartless and emotionless.

596
00:35:28,050 --> 00:35:29,670
The men of Yinshaluo Tribe

597
00:35:30,160 --> 00:35:31,079
cherish the warrior title

598
00:35:31,080 --> 00:35:32,860
more than their lives.

599
00:35:33,450 --> 00:35:34,500
That's right.

600
00:35:34,640 --> 00:35:38,110
When they return to their families,

601
00:35:39,160 --> 00:35:40,830
they're husbands

602
00:35:41,010 --> 00:35:42,580
and fathers.

603
00:35:43,050 --> 00:35:44,900
But I'm not envious of them at all.

604
00:35:45,080 --> 00:35:46,670
I'm happy about the fact

605
00:35:47,120 --> 00:35:49,710
that I can die together with you.

606
00:35:53,810 --> 00:35:55,369
Are you sure you're not Zhang Haike?

607
00:35:55,370 --> 00:35:57,380
That hurts.

608
00:36:03,080 --> 00:36:04,310
Naive,

609
00:36:04,890 --> 00:36:06,940
no matter how much you change,

610
00:36:07,530 --> 00:36:08,849
to me,

611
00:36:08,850 --> 00:36:10,380
you'll always be Naive.

612
00:36:11,530 --> 00:36:13,279
As long as I keep calling you Naive,

613
00:36:13,280 --> 00:36:14,559
I'm sure

614
00:36:14,560 --> 00:36:16,310
you'll return to normal one day.

615
00:36:22,680 --> 00:36:23,900
Let's go.

616
00:36:24,450 --> 00:36:26,329
Now, we're seeking death for real.

617
00:36:26,330 --> 00:36:28,750
Everything was meant to
build up to this moment.

618
00:36:31,010 --> 00:36:32,580
There's no room for negotiation now.

619
00:36:33,200 --> 00:36:34,790
What did you write

620
00:36:35,010 --> 00:36:36,350
in the 100-year-old tavern?

621
00:36:36,890 --> 00:36:39,639
I forgot. I forgot that I wrote
that I was going to face

622
00:36:39,640 --> 00:36:41,049
the Night King with Naive.

623
00:36:41,050 --> 00:36:43,670
It's either we die
or return alive together.

624
00:36:50,330 --> 00:36:52,020
This storm is ferocious.

625
00:36:52,200 --> 00:36:53,900
Therefore, we cannot hear each other

626
00:36:54,410 --> 00:36:56,350
when we're inside.

627
00:36:57,930 --> 00:37:00,079
I've come up with some simple gestures.

628
00:37:00,080 --> 00:37:01,719
We need to learn this
as soon as possible.

629
00:37:01,720 --> 00:37:04,110
Show me your hands.

630
00:37:05,370 --> 00:37:06,750
The first gesture,

631
00:37:07,010 --> 00:37:08,350
advance.

632
00:37:08,560 --> 00:37:10,540
That's right. Be more determined.

633
00:37:10,760 --> 00:37:11,639
The second gesture,

634
00:37:11,640 --> 00:37:12,790
retreat.

635
00:37:13,490 --> 00:37:15,009
We don't have a chance to retreat.

636
00:37:15,010 --> 00:37:16,790
Forget about this. Scrap that.

637
00:37:17,410 --> 00:37:18,630
No retreating allowed.

638
00:37:18,680 --> 00:37:19,759
Spread to the left and right?

639
00:37:19,760 --> 00:37:21,239
Look at the number of people we have.

640
00:37:21,240 --> 00:37:22,239
Scrap that as well.

641
00:37:22,240 --> 00:37:23,580
Be on standby?

642
00:37:23,810 --> 00:37:25,500
Do we even have time for that?

643
00:37:25,530 --> 00:37:26,580
Gather around!

644
00:37:27,850 --> 00:37:29,060
Gather around!

645
00:37:29,760 --> 00:37:30,790
Danger!

646
00:37:31,490 --> 00:37:32,830
Danger!

647
00:37:33,010 --> 00:37:34,279
Defeat the monster!

648
00:37:34,280 --> 00:37:36,150
Come, let's take a picture.

649
00:37:36,530 --> 00:37:38,159
I'll say "Yinshaluo Tribe."

650
00:37:38,160 --> 00:37:39,889
You guys will say "Cheese."

651
00:37:39,890 --> 00:37:41,119
Yinshaluo Tribe.

652
00:37:41,120 --> 00:37:42,630
Cheese!

653
00:37:44,970 --> 00:37:46,119
Yindan,

654
00:37:46,120 --> 00:37:47,809
Granny said the scouts

655
00:37:47,810 --> 00:37:48,849
never came back.

656
00:37:48,850 --> 00:37:50,369
She wants you to locate them.

657
00:37:50,370 --> 00:37:51,350
Let's go.

658
00:38:23,850 --> 00:38:25,060
What's going on?

659
00:38:29,640 --> 00:38:30,980
What happened?

660
00:38:31,760 --> 00:38:33,380
Something's off

661
00:38:33,850 --> 00:38:35,190
about the storm.

662
00:38:39,010 --> 00:38:41,190
Our scouts

663
00:38:41,490 --> 00:38:43,150
encountered strong winds

664
00:38:43,760 --> 00:38:45,790
on their way there.

665
00:38:48,890 --> 00:38:50,380
When I arrived,

666
00:38:52,240 --> 00:38:54,350
most of them were
already swept away by the storm.

667
00:38:54,890 --> 00:38:56,230
Granny.

668
00:38:57,720 --> 00:38:59,380
I did everything I could.

669
00:39:00,200 --> 00:39:02,460
But I only managed
to rescue a few of them.

670
00:39:05,530 --> 00:39:07,750
Feng, check the data.

671
00:39:13,450 --> 00:39:14,460
This is bad.

672
00:39:15,490 --> 00:39:17,060
The wind speed has increased.

673
00:39:17,760 --> 00:39:20,540
It's much faster than what we predicted.

674
00:39:20,850 --> 00:39:23,230
Maybe something has happened
to the underground heat source.

675
00:39:23,810 --> 00:39:25,460
How much time do we have left?

676
00:39:26,890 --> 00:39:28,880
We have until tomorrow afternoon
at the latest.

677
00:39:29,280 --> 00:39:32,009
The wind source will reach
the optimal detonation point by then.

678
00:39:32,010 --> 00:39:34,230
Now, I can join
the suicide squad, right?

679
00:39:34,600 --> 00:39:36,009
Yindan is injured.

680
00:39:36,010 --> 00:39:37,310
I'll replace him.

681
00:39:39,160 --> 00:39:39,809
Did you know

682
00:39:39,810 --> 00:39:41,639
why I didn't choose you from the start?

683
00:39:41,640 --> 00:39:42,790
I know.

684
00:39:43,160 --> 00:39:45,350
You want me to leave the place alive

685
00:39:45,490 --> 00:39:47,529
so that I can make it up to my regrets.

686
00:39:47,530 --> 00:39:48,630
You're wrong.

687
00:39:48,760 --> 00:39:50,350
It's because you can save more people

688
00:39:50,760 --> 00:39:52,670
when you're alive.

689
00:39:54,050 --> 00:39:56,190
If our operation fails,

690
00:39:57,050 --> 00:39:58,159
you're the only one

691
00:39:58,160 --> 00:40:00,230
who can take
all the information with you

692
00:40:00,370 --> 00:40:02,750
and show the outside world
what happened here.

693
00:40:02,930 --> 00:40:04,860
You are most familiar
with this piece of information.

694
00:40:05,330 --> 00:40:06,380
You are

695
00:40:06,930 --> 00:40:08,630
our last hope.

696
00:40:12,410 --> 00:40:13,849
Tell everyone to get ready.

697
00:40:13,850 --> 00:40:15,350
We'll depart tomorrow.

698
00:40:29,681 --> 00:40:32,951
♪Swept into a cold, relentless fate♪

699
00:40:33,191 --> 00:40:36,831
♪Which snow will conceal the mystery?♪

700
00:40:37,591 --> 00:40:42,281
♪Even if the chill is unavoidable♪

701
00:40:42,781 --> 00:40:45,021
♪I’ll ignite my obsession♪

702
00:40:45,211 --> 00:40:47,771
♪Until all the storms and snow subside♪

703
00:40:48,231 --> 00:40:49,931
♪No longer hiding♪

704
00:40:50,251 --> 00:40:53,061
♪That unknown miracle♪

705
00:40:53,681 --> 00:40:57,761
♪Only you will walk towards eternity♪

706
00:41:05,721 --> 00:41:09,881
♪Maybe the colors have long blurred♪

707
00:41:13,681 --> 00:41:17,991
♪Maybe they’ve long dissolved into chaos♪

708
00:41:24,661 --> 00:41:27,481
♪Forgetting the reason,
forgetting the outcome♪

709
00:41:27,681 --> 00:41:28,791
♪Why not forget it all?♪

710
00:41:28,791 --> 00:41:31,421
♪That scar, that shackle♪

711
00:41:31,731 --> 00:41:35,731
♪Let the storm sing praises,
storm, storm, storm♪

712
00:41:35,731 --> 00:41:40,491
♪Witness a brave heart shining bright♪

713
00:41:40,651 --> 00:41:43,481
♪Forgetting the reason,
forgetting the outcome♪

714
00:41:43,691 --> 00:41:47,481
♪But holding on even tighter,
no matter the ease or adversity♪

715
00:41:47,741 --> 00:41:52,721
♪Still stubborn, unrepentant,
storm, storm, storm♪

716
00:41:52,721 --> 00:41:56,411
♪Forgetting the return date,
but not this moment♪

717
00:42:13,681 --> 00:42:16,861
